  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;strong>Overview&lt;/strong>&lt;/font>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Rational SOMA 2.9 is a collection of four practices:&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.business.use_case_driven_business_modeling.base-ibm/guidances/practices/use_case_driven_business_modeling_7F800BA4.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_RO-zgDN6Ed6_nLybut0Zyw&quot;>Use Case Driven Business Modeling&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soa.service_identification.base-ibm/guidances/practices/service_identification_4932DF0E.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_GdFlkK9UEd2qXOsgZ_h9PA&quot;>Service Identification&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soa.service_specification.base-ibm/guidances/practices/service_specification_E8335628.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_S80AALaDEd2n36KPip6Xng&quot;>Service Specification&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soa.service_realization.base-ibm/guidances/practices/service_realization_3EA4F326.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_N9VOQLaDEd2n36KPip6Xng&quot;>Service Realization&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The three service-related practices collectively support what we refer to&amp;nbsp;as service&#xD;
    solution&amp;nbsp;design.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Their integrated use is more fully described in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../publish.soa.base-ibm/guidances/supportingmaterials/getting_started_with_the_soma_practices_5F55E72.html&quot;&#xD;
     guid=&quot;_jfluEEZHEd6DhbzzyJmhdQ&quot;>Developing Service-Oriented Solutions Using the Rational SOMA 2.9 practices&lt;/a>.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Essentially all successful service initiatives focus on tying the project artifacts back to the needs of the&#xD;
    business.&amp;nbsp; We provide the&amp;nbsp;Use Case Driven Business Modeling practice to help you produce some of the&#xD;
    business-oriented inputs that are needed to start service solution design, if you do not already have these.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The current service solution design practices are based upon the predecessor RUP SOMA 2.4 content.&amp;nbsp; They also&#xD;
    include substantial contributions from &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.soa.base-ibm/guidances/whitepapers/building_soa_solutions_redbook_BB469CB2.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_e3mR4FIREd6lNtylJFsPIg&quot;>Building SOA Solutions Using the Rational SDP&lt;/a>, including 12 &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.soa.base-ibm/guidances/concepts/soa_architectural_patterns_8FB91276.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_-Ne-cHhXEd63Mo-f0bVh9w&quot;>SOA Architectural best practices&lt;/a> (&quot;patterns&quot;) which are woven into the fabric of the&#xD;
    practices.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Guidelines for adopting the practices individually are presented in:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.business.use_case_driven_business_modeling.base-ibm/guidances/roadmaps/how_to_adopt_3425CC7D.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_wXcq4DN7Ed6_nLybut0Zyw&quot;>Roadmap: How to Adopt the Use Case Driven Business Modeling Practice&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soa.service_identification.base-ibm/guidances/roadmaps/how_to_adopt_service_identification_C1765C40.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_L2c_YFIVEd6lNtylJFsPIg&quot;>Roadmap: How to Adopt the Service Identification Practice&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soa.service_specification.base-ibm/guidances/roadmaps/how_to_adopt_service_specification_26814A8E.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_1c1xgGfrEd6Lp4pMdHNm6g&quot;>Roadmap: How to Adopt the Service Specification Practice&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.tech.soa.service_realization.base-ibm/guidances/roadmaps/how_to_adopt_service_realization_1B25ECBC.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_D1tzYGWuEd6Zd-lbA790BQ&quot;>Roadmap: How to Adopt the Service Realization Practice&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>Lifecycle Models for Service Solution Development&lt;/font>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    IBM's service lifecycle model contains four major activity groups:&amp;nbsp; Model, Assemble, Deploy, and Manage.&amp;nbsp; The&#xD;
    four Rational SOMA 2.9 practices&amp;nbsp;all support the &quot;Model&quot; (earliest) portion of the lifecycle.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    The&amp;nbsp;practices&amp;nbsp;can be used to support a number of service solution development lifecycle models,&amp;nbsp;three of&#xD;
    which are described in &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.soa.base-ibm/guidances/guidelines/service_development_lifecycle_models_408E8DED.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_NiIGsIYNEd6L7PopHG7zng&quot;>Guideline: Service Development Lifecycle Models&lt;/a>.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>&lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>Rational SOMA 2.9 Workflow&lt;/font>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    We present a suggested workflow that incorporates the four practices, &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../process.soa.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/rational_soma_29_workflow_AF81835B.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_8QNmoa2jEd6_dJstfLPnzA&quot;>here&lt;/a>. This particular lifecycle model is designed to support project-centric service&#xD;
    development initiatives.&amp;nbsp; The previously-mentioned guideline describes how these practices can be used to support&#xD;
    larger-scoped service efforts, as well.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;>&lt;strong>Changes and Improvements&lt;/strong>&lt;/font>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Principal changes and improvements in Rational SOMA 2.9 are:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Adoption of the Unified Method Architecture (UMA), which is compatible with the IBM Practice Library and makes it&#xD;
        easier to reuse and extend the practices;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Elimination of substantial content that was not clearly focused on service design.&amp;nbsp;Rational SOMA 2.9 is&#xD;
        smaller,&amp;nbsp;better organized,&amp;nbsp;and easier to comprehend than was RUP SOMA 2.4.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Adoption of the Object Management Group's &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.tech.soa.base-ibm/guidances/concepts/soaml_4074BA7B.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_XsWMIFIREd6lNtylJFsPIg&quot;>SoaML specification&lt;/a> for modeling service-oriented systems.&amp;nbsp; Content has&#xD;
        been cast or recast in terms of SoaML concepts and notations.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Service design advice and a service design&amp;nbsp;process that are more detailed than&amp;nbsp;RUP SOMA 2.4.&amp;nbsp; The&#xD;
        detailed steps of the process generally conform to the process that is described in &lt;em>Building SOA Solutions&#xD;
        Using the Rational SDP&lt;/em>.&amp;nbsp; We have further changed some process details to leverage&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;most&#xD;
        important constructs of SoaML.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        New tool mentors that describe how to&amp;nbsp;perform many of the design steps using IBM Rational Software Architect&#xD;
        for WebSphere Software, Version&amp;nbsp;7.5.4.&amp;nbsp; This version of the product provides a fairly rich set of&#xD;
        SoaML-compliant SOA design accelerators, as well as an expanded set of transforms (UML-to-artifact, and&#xD;
        artifact-to-UML) that support the SOA domain.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br />&#xD;
        &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
